Background

		Mr. Ronald J. Kramer, also known as Ron, has been the Chief Executive Officer of Griffon Corporation since April 2008. Mr. Kramer is a Owner of Clopay Building Products Company, Inc. He served as the President of Griffon Corporation from February 2009 to December 2012. Mr. Kramer served as President of Wynn Resorts Ltd. and Wynn Resorts (Macau) S.A from October 2002 to March 31, 2008. He served as the President of Wynn Las Vegas LLC. He served as President of Wynn Resorts ... Holdings LLC, a wholly owned indirect subsidiary of Wynn Resorts from April 2002 to October 2002. He was employed at Grand Casinos, Inc. He served as a Managing Director of Dresdner Kleinwort from July 1999 to October 2001. He served as Managing Director of Wasserstein Perella & Co., Inc. He served as Equity Analyst at Dresdner Kleinwort, Research Division. Mr. Kramer served as an Investment Banker for over twenty years with an experience of mergers and acquisitions and debt and equity financings. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Ladenberg Thalmann Group Inc. from May 1995 to July 1999. He served as the Chairman of Ladenberg Thalmann Group Inc. from February 1986 to July 1999. He has been a Vice Chairman of Griffon Corporation, an affiliate of Ames True Temper Inc. since November 2003. He has been a Director of New Valley LLC since November 1994, Griffon Corporation since 1993 and Sapphire Industrials Corp. since October 2007. Mr. Kramer serves as a Director of Lakes Gaming Inc. He served as a Director of Golden Entertainment, Inc. since June 1998. He served as a Director of Monster Worldwide Inc. from February 2000 to December 27, 2009 and served as its Lead Independent Director until December 27, 2009. He served as a Director of Wynn Resorts Ltd from October 2002 to March 31, 2008 and Wynn Resorts (Macau) S.A. from April 2002 to March 17, 2008 and Leap Wireless International Inc. from November 3, 2009 to March 13, 2014. He served as a Director of Ladenberg Thalmann Group Inc. He served as a Director of Lakes Entertainment Inc. since June 1998. He served as a Director of Wynn Las Vegas, LLC. He served as a Trustee of Republic Property Trust since January 13, 2006. He has been Director of the Mt. Sinai Children's Center Foundation since 1999. Mr. Kramer holds a Bachelor of Science Degree in Economics from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and a Master of Business Administration from New York University.Read Full Background




