“Illinois Becomes Second State In Nation To Bar Employers From Obtaining Access To Employee Social Networking Pages,” One Minute Memo, Seyfarth Shaw LLP (August 10, 2012)

“Supreme Court Wades Into The Fray As To Public Sector Unions’ Use Of Non-Member Fees For Ideological Purposes, “ One Minute Memo, Seyfarth Shaw LLP (June 22, 2012)

		Chapter co-editor, Chapter 10, “Postelection Procedures,” How to Take a Case Before the NLRB (7th Ed. 2000, 2003 and 2005 Supp., 8th Ed. 2008)

		Co-author, Chapter 3 “Obligations under the National Labor Relations Act.”  Labor and Employment Issues in Transactions, Business Restructuring, and Workforce Reductions (Ill. Inst. for CLE 2nd Ed. 2008)

		Contributing Editor, Labor and Employment Law:  The Employer’s Compliance Guide (Thompson 2008)

		Co-author, “Garcetti v. Ceballos:  The Battle over What It Means Has Just Begun,” 39 Urban Law No. 4, 983 (2007)

		Co-author, “Pension Fund Litigation:  Not Just for the Public Sector,” NPELRA Newsletter (Nov. 2007)

		Co-author, “Employment Discrimination Law” 40-3rd C.P.S. (BNA 2006)

		Co-author, Chapter 10 “Municipal Personnel Practices,” Illinois Municipal Law (Ill. Inst. For LE 2006)

